docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:186:| [DEPLOYMENT_MANIFEST.md](./DEPLOYMENT_MANIFEST.md) | Which script deploys which contract |
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:195:VFIDE supports deployment to Base mainnet, Polygon mainnet, and zkSync Era mainnet (plus their respective testnets). Each chain is a **separate deployment**: contracts must be deployed on every chain you want to support, and the frontend must be configured with chain-scoped envvars to route transactions correctly.
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:197:### Per-chain deploy procedure
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:202:# Set the deployer's RPC/keys for THIS chain
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:206:# 1. Run the standard deploy script
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:207:npx hardhat run scripts/deploy-full.ts --network <chain-name>
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:209:# 2. Capture the deployed addresses (deploy-full.ts checkpoints to .deployments/<chain>.json per OP-2)
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:210:cat .deployments/<chain-name>.json
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:219:# 5. Run post-deploy validation
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:220:npm run -s validate:deploy -- --network <chain-name>
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:225:After deploying to all target chains, populate the frontend env with chain-scoped addresses. See `ENV_CONTRACT_ADDRESS_MATRIX.md` for the full list and pattern.
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:238:Run `npm run -s validate:env -- --multi-chain` before deploying the frontend.
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:246:2. **Single-chain mode**: the original `lib/indexer/service.ts` continues to work for single-chain deploys. Set `NEXT_PUBLIC_CHAIN_ID` to the target chain.
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:261:4. Update the frontend deploy. Because envvars are validated at deploy-time, the deploy will fail-fast if any contract is missing for any chain.
docs/DEPLOYMENT.md:263:6. Communicate the addition publicly. Document the new chain in `KEY_MANAGEMENT_PLAN.md` (each chain has its own deployer and admin role chain-of-custody).
docs/DEPLOYMENT_MANIFEST.md:3:This document maps every production Solidity contract to its deployment mechanism.
