docs/ENV_CONTRACT_ADDRESS_MATRIX.md:61:When VFIDE is deployed to more than one chain (Base + Polygon + zkSync, for example), every contract address envvar **must** be set in chain-scoped form. Without this, the frontend silently falls back to the unscoped envvar — which holds the address from a different chain — and transactions fail or land in the wrong place.
docs/ENV_CONTRACT_ADDRESS_MATRIX.md:74:# Single-chain deploy (Base mainnet only, default fallback works)
docs/ENV_CONTRACT_ADDRESS_MATRIX.md:77:# Multi-chain deploy: set BOTH the unscoped (acts as default) AND each chain's scoped form
docs/ENV_CONTRACT_ADDRESS_MATRIX.md:100:### Required envvar for multi-chain deploys
