docs/SYSTEM_FEATURE_REVIEW_TRACKER.md:81:  - constructor now sets `initialized = true`, preventing post-deploy takeover via `initialize(...)` on constructor-deployed vaults.
docs/SYSTEM_FEATURE_REVIEW_TRACKER.md:109:  - `contracts/VaultHub.sol` constructor now rejects zero `vfideToken` and zero `dao` addresses, preventing deployment-time bricking of core vault/DAO recovery wiring.
docs/SYSTEM_FEATURE_REVIEW_TRACKER.md:132:  - constructor now rejects zero `dao` address (`PM: zero DAO`), preventing invalid governance wiring at deployment time.
docs/SYSTEM_FEATURE_REVIEW_TRACKER.md:149:  - `contracts/VFIDEBridge.sol` constructor now rejects zero `endpoint` and zero `owner` addresses in addition to existing token guard, preventing invalid deployment wiring for omnichain messaging/ownership.
docs/SYSTEM_FEATURE_REVIEW_TRACKER.md:168:- Canonical path alignment completed: `VaultHub` deploys `contracts/UserVault.sol`, and Chain-of-Return local verifier now targets `artifacts/contracts/UserVault.sol/UserVault.json`.
docs/SYSTEM_FEATURE_REVIEW_TRACKER.md:230:- Updated vault health aggregate to include `operationsPool` and tracked legacy outflows in `totalIn`, keeping health totals internally coherent.
